newsitem.title: MALAYSIA: Malaysian rubber prices barely changed at close.
newsitem.headline: Malaysian rubber prices barely changed at close.

text.p: Malaysian rubber prices were barely changed at the close as both buyers and sellers were unwilling to commit themselves at current levels, dealers said.
They said the market was also trying to shake off the effects of the long holiday weekend. The local rubber market was closed on Monday for a Hindu festival.
"There were no bids at all today while offer prices were maintained," a local dealer said. "Market players are playing a waiting game."
He said while buyers stayed at the sidelines, producers were also not keen to sell due to rains in some crop areas.

At the close, December RSS1 buyer was quoted at 320.50 cents ($1.27) a kg by the Malaysian Rubber Exchange and Licensing Board, down half cent from Friday. December SMR 20 buyer was unchanged at 310.50 cents ($1.23) a kg.
Traders retained previous offer prices, quoting the SMR CV at 366 cents, SMR L at 344, SMR 5 at 322, SMR 10 at 311, SMR 20 at 310 and drum latex at 237.
The INRO five-day moving average was 245.49 Malaysian/Singapore cents per kg on Nov 11 against 245.37 on Nov 8. The daily indicator price was 245.65 versus 246.17.
